# Phase <N> — <title>

> Work item: [`../spec.md`](../spec.md) • Progress (status of record): [`../progress.md`](../progress.md)
> Phase order: <N> of <total>  •  Parallel with: <other phase numbers or "none">

A phase is one coherent, reviewable, low-risk increment of the work item. It contains one or more
**iterations** (each ~1 PR). Iterations within a phase are sequential by default unless explicitly
parallelizable.

> **Single source of truth for status:** [`../progress.md`](../progress.md). This file describes
> what each iteration *is* — scope, files, acceptance — not what state it's in. Phase status and
> per-iteration status live in `progress.md`'s tables; mirroring them here only invites drift.

If a constraint or blocker forces this phase's shape to change, update this file in place (scope,
acceptance, file lists) and append a diary entry naming what changed and why. Don't delete the
old shape silently.

